node.title: takes a turn
node.description: colorful cascade makes a hard turn above the falls at bains gap

node.title: contrast
node.description: during the summer drought there's been virtually no water coming off the rock dam below bains gap falls.  this little fall is all that's left, but is a great contrast between the mossy boulder and man-made dam.  i really like the curves in the fallen limb and how it parallels the fall.

node.title: fun guys
node.description: -striking row of mushrooms along the fiery gizzard trail in SE Tennessee

node.title: little river falls
node.description: Even during a drought, the falls at little river canyon are quite breathtaking.  I waited quite awhile, but finally got a shot without swimmers, sunbathers, or other sightseers.
